<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880829-0050 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Sherwood Group Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> SHD </CO><IN> ERN </IN><TEXT>   Sherwood Group Inc., citing &quot;very significant losses&quot; from its retail brokerage offices, said it had a net loss of $33.8 million in the fourth quarter ended May 31, compared with year-earlier net income of $2.3 million, or 37 cents a share. Revenue fell 81% to $5.4 million from $29 million.    The financial services company, which makes a market in more than 3,300 over-the-counter securities, said its loss from retail branch offices and costs of terminating clearing operations totaled $19.7 million in the quarter. The retail offices were sold in May.    In the year ended May 31, the company had a net loss of $40.1 million compared with year-earlier profit of $3.6 million, or 59 cents a share. Revenue fell 17% to $48.5 million from $58.1 million. </TEXT></DOC>